.el .ds Aq '
.TH cdf-backfill 1  "cdf-backfill "
.SH NAME
cdf\-backfill \- Plan or execute a bounded cursor backfill
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcdf backfill\fR [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-\-resource\fR] [\fB\-\-from\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-\-to\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-color\fR] [\fB\-\-target\fR] [\fB\-\-execute\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-slice\-size\fR] [\fB\-\-unicode\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIRESOURCE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Plan or execute a bounded cursor backfill
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress progress and non\-primary success narration
.TP
\fB\-\-resource\fR \fI<RESOURCE>\fR
Resource identifier (compatibility form)
.TP
\fB\-\-from\fR \fI<CURSOR>\fR
Inclusive cursor lower bound
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show evidence detail; repeat for diagnostics
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR
Color policy: auto, always, or never
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR \fI<CURSOR>\fR
Destination URI or cursor upper bound, as shown in usage
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-color\fR
Compatibility alias for \-\-color never
.TP
\fB\-\-target\fR \fI<TARGET>\fR
Destination target/table compatibility option
.TP
\fB\-\-execute\fR
Apply the planned operation
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR
Progress policy: auto, always, or never
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-slice\-size\fR \fI<N>\fR
Rows per backfill slice
.TP
\fB\-\-unicode\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR
Unicode policy: auto, always, or never
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fIRESOURCE\fR]
Resource identifier
